remarks: similar to, or is, either Harpalus fuscipalpus or Harpalus carbonatus. ~10 mm long. Basal fovea more convex. Sparsely punctate. Posterior pronotal corners rounded but defined with small overlap onto elytra.
~8 mm in lenth. Very rounded pronotal posterior angles with more severe curvature near head, narrow head. Legs rufous.
~5 mm in length. Amara sp? 2 orbital setae, pronotum with somewhat parallel sides, brassy iridescence overall. Amara cupreolata or A. convexa?
